  "prompt": "In GOT, if I walked to Storms End, knocked on the door and asked who's in charge, what would they say?",
  "response": "This depends heavily on **when** you arrive at Storm's End! Here's a breakdown based on different periods in *Game of Thrones*:\n\n*   **During Robert's Rebellion (Before Season 1):**\n    *   **Stannis Baratheon:** He was given Storm's End to hold against the Tyrells and Redwyne's. If you arrived during the siege, it would have been Stannis commanding his men.\n\n*   **Early Season 1:**\n    *   **Renly Baratheon:** The \"Lord of Storm's End\", although he preferred court life in King's Landing and rarely stayed there.\n\n*   **Late Season 1 - Mid Season 2:**\n    *   **Stannis Baratheon (Claimant):** After Renly declared himself king, Stannis also claims the Iron Throne, but is still the head of House Baratheon. In his eyes, Storm's End is rightfully his. While Stannis focuses his war efforts elsewhere, he would still be the Lord of Storm's End, by law and by force.\n    *   **Cortnay Penrose (Castellan/Warden):** A loyal supporter of Renly and the true defender of Storm's End at this time. Penrose commands the garrison. If you asked, he would be the one to respond, and would likely give his name and title and ask why you were at Storm's End.\n\n*   **Late Season 2 - Season 3:**\n    *   **Stannis Baratheon (After the Shadow Baby):** Cortnay Penrose is dead, murdered by Melisandre's shadow baby. Stannis gains control of the castle.\n\n*   **Season 4 - Season 5:**\n    *   **Stannis Baratheon (By Right):** Technically, Stannis remains Lord of Storm's End by right of conquest and Baratheon blood. However, he is occupied with his campaign in the North, so the castle is either under garrison control or possibly abandoned.\n\n*   **Season 6 - End of Series:**\n    *   **No One:** After Stannis's death at the hands of Brienne of Tarth, House Baratheon is effectively extinct. Storm's End reverts to the Crown. Who is in charge at this point is unclear. Most likely, it would be a Castellan appointed by the Iron Throne or the new King Bran. Given his history, Gendry may well have been given the castle.\n\nTherefore, depending on the time you ask, the answer could be:\n\n*   \"Lord Stannis Baratheon.\"\n*   \"Lord Renly Baratheon.\"\n*   \"Castellan Cortnay Penrose, in the name of King Renly.\"\n*   \"[Rank and Name] commanding the garrison, under the authority of King [Ruler of the Iron Throne at the time].\"\n*   \"No one. Storm's End is under the authority of the Crown.\"\n*   \"Lord Gendry Baratheon\" (Most probable if it is the end of the series).\n\nThe most prudent answer would be to approach with caution and be respectful of the Baratheon household!\n",
